      "content": "it just feels so cruel that everyone keeps pushing for more \"treatment\" and more \"fighting\" when all that does is prolong the agony. it's like people think being alive is some kind of mandatory duty even when life is just suffering. if there's no way to fix it, isn't it more compassionate to let someone just rest? it feels like the only way to actually achieve any kind of mercy is to just exit.",
